  "artwork_generated_url": "",
  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 7.17,
      "text": "스크린 잉글리쉬"
    },
    {
      "start": 7.17,
      "end": 28.03,
      "text": "GMP Morning Theater 스크린 잉글리쉬 타임"
    },
    {
      "start": 28.03,
      "end": 29.97,
      "text": "9월에 함께하고 있는 영화는"
    },
    {
      "start": 29.97,
      "end": 34.63,
      "text": "A well-meaning yet surprisingly bland coming-of-age 드라마리"
    },
    {
      "start": 34.63,
      "end": 37.23,
      "text": "Abe, Abe의 쿠킹 다이어리"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.23,
      "end": 39.47,
      "text": "와우, 경쾌하게 인사해주셨습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 39.77,
      "end": 41.35,
      "text": "크리스 씨, 안녕하세요."
    },
    {
      "start": 41.77,
      "end": 42.77,
      "text": "Good morning, 안녕하세요."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.39,
      "end": 44.27,
      "text": "Hello, hello."
    },
    {
      "start": 44.39,
      "end": 47.51,
      "text": "네, 제가 도입에 이렇게 이야기를 했잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 48.67,
      "end": 51.57,
      "text": "Coming-of-age 드라마리"
    },
    {
      "start": 51.57,
      "end": 52.17,
      "text": "그쵸?"
    },
    {
      "start": 52.29,
      "end": 53.45,
      "text": "Coming-of-age"
    },
    {
      "start": 53.45,
      "end": 56.51,
      "text": "We all come to that time"
    },
    {
      "start": 56.51,
      "end": 56.93,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 56.93,
      "end": 58.45,
      "text": "When we come of age"
    },
    {
      "start": 58.45,
      "end": 61.61,
      "text": "드라마리라는 단어에 대해서"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.61,
      "end": 63.83,
      "text": "처음 들어보시는 분들이 좀 계실 것 같은데"
    },
    {
      "start": 63.83,
      "end": 64.73,
      "text": "드라마리, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.81,
      "end": 66.55,
      "text": "Yeah, but isn't it deducible?"
    },
    {
      "start": 67.05,
      "end": 67.29,
      "text": "그쵸?"
    },
    {
      "start": 67.37,
      "end": 68.15,
      "text": "Can you guess?"
    },
    {
      "start": 68.25,
      "end": 68.45,
      "text": "Oh"
    },
    {
      "start": 68.45,
      "end": 71.01,
      "text": "드라마, 디, 드라마디"
    },
    {
      "start": 71.01,
      "end": 73.29,
      "text": "드라마 플러스 코미디"
    },
    {
      "start": 73.29,
      "end": 73.77,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 73.77,
      "end": 76.01,
      "text": "Yeah, it's like a fusion word."
    },
    {
      "start": 76.11,
      "end": 77.15,
      "text": "Yeah, 맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 77.87,
      "end": 80.31,
      "text": "제목과 그리고 이 내용과"
    },
    {
      "start": 80.31,
      "end": 82.83,
      "text": "그리고 좀 전에 제가 묘사를 한 이 단어까지"
    },
    {
      "start": 82.83,
      "end": 86.23,
      "text": "뭔가 다 퓨전에 관련된 것들이 뭉쳐져 있어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 86.23,
      "end": 86.63,
      "text": "그쵸?"
    },
    {
      "start": 86.71,
      "end": 87.77,
      "text": "Yeah, just like this movie"
    },
    {
      "start": 87.77,
      "end": 89.33,
      "text": "is about fusion cooking."
    },
    {
      "start": 89.43,
      "end": 89.75,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 90.11,
      "end": 92.01,
      "text": "So, 드라마디 is a nice fusion word"
    },
    {
      "start": 92.01,
      "end": 92.91,
      "text": "for this movie."
    },
    {
      "start": 93.11,
      "end": 93.85,
      "text": "그러고 보니까"
    },
    {
      "start": 93.85,
      "end": 95.17,
      "text": "이 fusion이라는 말을요"
    },
    {
      "start": 95.17,
      "end": 97.33,
      "text": "우리가 무심코 참 많이 쓰게 되는 것 같은데"
    },
    {
      "start": 97.33,
      "end": 100.55,
      "text": "이번 기회에 이 단어에 대해서"
    },
    {
      "start": 100.55,
      "end": 102.51,
      "text": "조금 더 살펴보면 좋을 것 같은데"
    },
    {
      "start": 102.51,
      "end": 104.43,
      "text": "Do you know the origin of this word?"
    },
    {
      "start": 104.83,
      "end": 106.31,
      "text": "Yes, I did my homework."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.49,
      "end": 107.17,
      "text": "Oh, really?"
    },
    {
      "start": 107.65,
      "end": 109.89,
      "text": "I studied the origin of the word."
    },
    {
      "start": 110.09,
      "end": 112.41,
      "text": "그래서 어디에서 이 오리진이 생겼나요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 112.87,
      "end": 114.77,
      "text": "Like many, many English words,"
    },
    {
      "start": 115.01,
      "end": 116.67,
      "text": "it's based, it's from Latin."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.85,
      "end": 117.25,
      "text": "Yeah, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 117.51,
      "end": 120.49,
      "text": "And it comes from the Latin word fundir"
    },
    {
      "start": 120.49,
      "end": 122.11,
      "text": "meaning melt."
    },
    {
      "start": 122.75,
      "end": 124.33,
      "text": "Oh, fundir?"
    },
    {
      "start": 124.51,
      "end": 126.15,
      "text": "이게 라틴어 발음인가요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 126.27,
      "end": 127.89,
      "text": "I'm not sure the exact pronunciation."
    },
    {
      "start": 127.89,
      "end": 131.37,
      "text": "But the spelling is F-U-N-D-E-R-E"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.37,
      "end": 132.57,
      "text": "Oh, I see."
    },
    {
      "start": 132.69,
      "end": 133.67,
      "text": "And it means to melt."
    },
    {
      "start": 133.91,
      "end": 136.15,
      "text": "So, fusion is the melting"
    },
    {
      "start": 136.15,
      "end": 138.17,
      "text": "of two things together."
    },
    {
      "start": 138.55,
      "end": 140.61,
      "text": "Like music or food,"
    },
    {
      "start": 140.61,
      "end": 142.45,
      "text": "it could be more than two things."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.93,
      "end": 144.21,
      "text": "But anyways, melting"
    },
    {
      "start": 144.21,
      "end": 145.81,
      "text": "more than one thing together."
    },
    {
      "start": 146.55,
      "end": 147.49,
      "text": "And also in science,"
    },
    {
      "start": 147.67,
      "end": 148.89,
      "text": "fusion is the process"
    },
    {
      "start": 148.89,
      "end": 150.71,
      "text": "of merging atoms together"
    },
    {
      "start": 150.71,
      "end": 152.65,
      "text": "to create energy."
    },
    {
      "start": 152.93,
      "end": 154.87,
      "text": "와, 좀 어렵게 느껴지십니까?"
    },
    {
      "start": 154.87,
      "end": 156.59,
      "text": "이 핵융합은 원자들이"
    },
    {
      "start": 156.59,
      "end": 157.99,
      "text": "서로 합쳐지는 과정이다."
    },
    {
      "start": 158.19,
      "end": 158.93,
      "text": "이런 상황에서도"
    },
    {
      "start": 158.93,
      "end": 160.51,
      "text": "이 fusion이라는 단어로"
    },
    {
      "start": 160.51,
      "end": 161.43,
      "text": "나타낼 수가 있는데"
    },
    {
      "start": 161.43,
      "end": 162.75,
      "text": "You know, I remember"
    },
    {
      "start": 162.75,
      "end": 163.67,
      "text": "the little boy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 163.99,
      "end": 164.93,
      "text": "Max,"
    },
    {
      "start": 165.43,
      "end": 166.79,
      "text": "from the previous movie."
    },
    {
      "start": 167.03,
      "end": 167.49,
      "text": "Max?"
    },
    {
      "start": 167.57,
      "end": 168.87,
      "text": "Yeah, monster family"
    },
    {
      "start": 168.87,
      "end": 170.05,
      "text": "and Max가"
    },
    {
      "start": 170.05,
      "end": 170.83,
      "text": "The little boy."
    },
    {
      "start": 170.97,
      "end": 173.31,
      "text": "Yeah, he used this word once."
    },
    {
      "start": 173.61,
      "end": 173.91,
      "text": "Really?"
    },
    {
      "start": 174.17,
      "end": 176.99,
      "text": "He's very, very smart."
    },
    {
      "start": 177.13,
      "end": 178.27,
      "text": "And he loves science."
    },
    {
      "start": 178.43,
      "end": 179.83,
      "text": "So, he would use this word."
    },
    {
      "start": 179.85,
      "end": 180.17,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 180.43,
      "end": 181.49,
      "text": "역시 똑똑했던"
    },
    {
      "start": 181.49,
      "end": 182.79,
      "text": "그 몬스터 패밀리의"
    },
    {
      "start": 182.79,
      "end": 185.23,
      "text": "Max라는 친구도 생각이 납니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 185.23,
      "end": 187.09,
      "text": "다 잊어버리신 거 아니겠죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 187.75,
      "end": 188.27,
      "text": "Max?"
    },
    {
      "start": 188.47,
      "end": 189.15,
      "text": "오, 오케이."
    },
    {
      "start": 189.53,
      "end": 191.13,
      "text": "자, 오늘 장면 듣고 오겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 191.51,
      "end": 193.3,
      "text": "I don't know what to do."
    },
    {
      "start": 193.9,
      "end": 194.74,
      "text": "It's okay."
    },
    {
      "start": 195.28,
      "end": 197.18,
      "text": "There is no guidebook."
    },
    {
      "start": 197.7,
      "end": 198.6,
      "text": "To be a parent."
    },
    {
      "start": 199.31,
      "end": 200.29,
      "text": "Hard to be one."
    },
    {
      "start": 200.89,
      "end": 202.19,
      "text": "And hard to lose one."
    },
    {
      "start": 203.14,
      "end": 204.54,
      "text": "He will come home, huh, baby?"
    },
    {
      "start": 205.86,
      "end": 206.58,
      "text": "It's so..."
    },
    {
      "start": 206.58,
      "end": 213.95,
      "text": "You should eat something."
    },
    {
      "start": 213.95,
      "end": 221.65,
      "text": "Yeah, this is the drama part"
    },
    {
      "start": 221.65,
      "end": 222.77,
      "text": "of the dramedy."
    },
    {
      "start": 222.91,
      "end": 223.59,
      "text": "Yeah, that's right."
    },
    {
      "start": 223.59,
      "end": 224.61,
      "text": "Not the comedy part."
    },
    {
      "start": 224.93,
      "end": 226.43,
      "text": "Things are very serious."
    },
    {
      "start": 227.23,
      "end": 228.39,
      "text": "Abe went missing."
    },
    {
      "start": 229.07,
      "end": 230.37,
      "text": "Remember, they were fighting"
    },
    {
      "start": 230.37,
      "end": 231.29,
      "text": "at the dinner table?"
    },
    {
      "start": 231.37,
      "end": 231.57,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 231.79,
      "end": 233.03,
      "text": "A huge fight."
    },
    {
      "start": 233.17,
      "end": 233.29,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 233.59,
      "end": 234.41,
      "text": "And Abe was trying"
    },
    {
      "start": 234.41,
      "end": 235.31,
      "text": "to cook the turkey,"
    },
    {
      "start": 235.51,
      "end": 236.63,
      "text": "but he listened"
    },
    {
      "start": 236.63,
      "end": 237.41,
      "text": "to them fighting."
    },
    {
      "start": 237.77,
      "end": 239.33,
      "text": "He blamed himself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 239.55,
      "end": 241.27,
      "text": "and he just ran away"
    },
    {
      "start": 241.27,
      "end": 242.89,
      "text": "while his parents"
    },
    {
      "start": 242.89,
      "end": 243.59,
      "text": "and relatives"
    },
    {
      "start": 243.59,
      "end": 244.75,
      "text": "were arguing."
    },
    {
      "start": 244.97,
      "end": 245.31,
      "text": "Right."
    },
    {
      "start": 245.93,
      "end": 247.05,
      "text": "Abe가 진짜"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.05,
      "end": 248.65,
      "text": "집에서 가출을 해버리는"
    },
    {
      "start": 248.65,
      "end": 249.99,
      "text": "그런 상황이"
    },
    {
      "start": 249.99,
      "end": 250.93,
      "text": "연출이 되는데요."
    },
    {
      "start": 251.85,
      "end": 253.21,
      "text": "아무래도 가족들과"
    },
    {
      "start": 253.21,
      "end": 254.59,
      "text": "너무 심하게 논쟁을 하는"
    },
    {
      "start": 254.59,
      "end": 256.01,
      "text": "모습들을 많이 봤기 때문에"
    },
    {
      "start": 256.01,
      "end": 256.93,
      "text": "그런 것 같습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 257.13,
      "end": 257.31,
      "text": "그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 257.55,
      "end": 257.93,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 258.11,
      "end": 259.13,
      "text": "So now they're all"
    },
    {
      "start": 259.13,
      "end": 260.73,
      "text": "Oh, what should we do?"
    },
    {
      "start": 261.21,
      "end": 261.95,
      "text": "And they're realizing"
    },
    {
      "start": 261.95,
      "end": 262.97,
      "text": "what is important"
    },
    {
      "start": 262.97,
      "end": 264.33,
      "text": "in their lives."
    },
    {
      "start": 264.33,
      "end": 265.41,
      "text": "It's actually..."
    },
    {
      "start": 265.41,
      "end": 267.01,
      "text": "They're actually getting along"
    },
    {
      "start": 267.01,
      "end": 268.47,
      "text": "after Abe leaves."
    },
    {
      "start": 268.55,
      "end": 268.87,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 269.11,
      "end": 269.87,
      "text": "It's kind of funny."
    },
    {
      "start": 269.87,
      "end": 271.75,
      "text": "저는 이 장면을 들으면서요."
    },
    {
      "start": 271.99,
      "end": 272.95,
      "text": "이 가족관계는"
    },
    {
      "start": 272.95,
      "end": 275.03,
      "text": "마치 계절과도 같다,"
    },
    {
      "start": 275.19,
      "end": 276.37,
      "text": "사계절과도 같다"
    },
    {
      "start": 276.37,
      "end": 277.33,
      "text": "이런 생각을 했어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 277.43,
      "end": 278.21,
      "text": "Like the four seasons?"
    },
    {
      "start": 278.33,
      "end": 278.63,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 279.39,
      "end": 280.25,
      "text": "봄도 있고,"
    },
    {
      "start": 280.35,
      "end": 280.87,
      "text": "여름도 있고,"
    },
    {
      "start": 280.95,
      "end": 281.43,
      "text": "가을도 있고,"
    },
    {
      "start": 281.51,
      "end": 282.17,
      "text": "겨울도 있고."
    },
    {
      "start": 282.59,
      "end": 283.75,
      "text": "So it's like winter"
    },
    {
      "start": 283.75,
      "end": 284.47,
      "text": "for him now."
    },
    {
      "start": 284.65,
      "end": 285.05,
      "text": "Aha."
    },
    {
      "start": 285.13,
      "end": 285.41,
      "text": "그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.59,
      "end": 286.15,
      "text": "For Abe."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.31,
      "end": 286.57,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.71,
      "end": 287.33,
      "text": "He's sad,"
    },
    {
      "start": 287.65,
      "end": 288.17,
      "text": "depressed."
    },
    {
      "start": 288.45,
      "end": 288.79,
      "text": "Right."
    },
    {
      "start": 288.95,
      "end": 290.21,
      "text": "Yeah, he's on a rollercoaster."
    },
    {
      "start": 290.29,
      "end": 291.45,
      "text": "이거 괜찮은 표현 아닌가요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 291.99,
      "end": 293.69,
      "text": "I can understand it."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.07,
      "end": 294.23,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.45,
      "end": 295.17,
      "text": "굽이굽이 있어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 295.21,
      "end": 295.49,
      "text": "그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 295.75,
      "end": 296.57,
      "text": "Sometimes it's hot."
    },
    {
      "start": 296.77,
      "end": 297.89,
      "text": "Sometimes it's cold."
    },
    {
      "start": 298.01,
      "end": 298.21,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 298.45,
      "end": 299.57,
      "text": "Sometimes it's in between."
    },
    {
      "start": 299.87,
      "end": 301.07,
      "text": "I can understand."
    },
    {
      "start": 301.17,
      "end": 301.29,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 301.49,
      "end": 302.79,
      "text": "겨울이 지나고 봄이 오지만,"
    },
    {
      "start": 303.15,
      "end": 304.77,
      "text": "또 다시 겨울이 올 수도 있다는 거."
    },
    {
      "start": 304.89,
      "end": 305.05,
      "text": "그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.47,
      "end": 307.99,
      "text": "스스로 생각해서 굉장히 행복합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 308.33,
      "end": 309.43,
      "text": "After winter comes spring."
    },
    {
      "start": 309.57,
      "end": 310.69,
      "text": "Spring is coming."
    },
    {
      "start": 310.95,
      "end": 311.17,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 311.71,
      "end": 313.81,
      "text": "어떤 단어들이 있었는지 좀 들어볼까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 314.25,
      "end": 314.93,
      "text": "Guidebook."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.03,
      "end": 315.17,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.43,
      "end": 316.07,
      "text": "Guidebook."
    },
    {
      "start": 316.43,
      "end": 317.19,
      "text": "어렵지 않으시죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 317.19,
      "end": 325.35,
      "text": "특히 여행에 관련되어서 안내서, 지침서라고도 쓰이고, 그냥 안내서 혹은 지침서라고도 해석하실 수 있습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 325.71,
      "end": 327.05,
      "text": "Losing steam."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.15,
      "end": 328.81,
      "text": "이거 되게 재미있는 표현인 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 328.89,
      "end": 330.09,
      "text": "I like this one."
    },
    {
      "start": 330.33,
      "end": 331.47,
      "text": "I'm losing steam."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.65,
      "end": 332.41,
      "text": "종종 그러세요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 332.65,
      "end": 333.29,
      "text": "Yeah, sure."
    },
    {
      "start": 333.29,
      "end": 335.97,
      "text": "주로 언제, 어떨 때?"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.13,
      "end": 343.47,
      "text": "When I'm trying to read a book to my daughter, and she says, read another one, and then another one, and another one."
    },
    {
      "start": 343.53,
      "end": 344.49,
      "text": "I'm losing steam."
    },
    {
      "start": 344.59,
      "end": 345.07,
      "text": "Come on."
    },
    {
      "start": 345.11,
      "end": 345.41,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 345.59,
      "end": 346.23,
      "text": "Parenting."
    },
    {
      "start": 346.39,
      "end": 347.19,
      "text": "정말 어렵죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 347.27,
      "end": 347.83,
      "text": "Go to bed."
    },
    {
      "start": 347.83,
      "end": 358.45,
      "text": "여기에서의 steam이라는 단어는요, 우리가 소위 알고 있는 기미나 혹은 증기에 관련된 것이 아니고, 기력에 관련된 것이라고 생각하시면 해석하시기가 편해요."
    },
    {
      "start": 358.77,
      "end": 364.15,
      "text": "그래서 losing steam이라고 했으니까, 기력이 쇄하다, 기력을 잃다라는 겁니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 365.57,
      "end": 367.11,
      "text": "I can't see straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 367.49,
      "end": 368.31,
      "text": "알고도 많이 써요."
    },
    {
      "start": 368.37,
      "end": 368.83,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 368.97,
      "end": 369.99,
      "text": "I can't see straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 369.99,
      "end": 375.39,
      "text": "뭔가 굉장히 좌절하고 낭망하고 정신이 없을 때, I can't see straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 375.61,
      "end": 377.19,
      "text": "이런 표현들 쓸 수 있을 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 377.19,
      "end": 381.37,
      "text": "뭔가를 제대로 볼 수 없다, 혹은 똑바로 볼 수 없다라는 의미죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 381.45,
      "end": 385.07,
      "text": "If you're really, really stressed and worried about something, I see."
    },
    {
      "start": 385.31,
      "end": 387.47,
      "text": "Oftentimes, you can't see straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 387.71,
      "end": 389.15,
      "text": "I can't see straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 389.27,
      "end": 390.39,
      "text": "유용한 표현이겠죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 390.91,
      "end": 392.27,
      "text": "이 내용 한 번 더 들어보겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 393.33,
      "end": 394.61,
      "text": "I don't know what to do."
    },
    {
      "start": 395.43,
      "end": 396.01,
      "text": "It's okay."
    },
    {
      "start": 396.01,
      "end": 398.47,
      "text": "There is no guidebook."
    },
    {
      "start": 399.01,
      "end": 399.89,
      "text": "To be a parent."
    },
    {
      "start": 400.61,
      "end": 401.57,
      "text": "Hard to be one."
    },
    {
      "start": 402.19,
      "end": 403.47,
      "text": "And hard to lose one."
    },
    {
      "start": 404.43,
      "end": 405.83,
      "text": "He will come home, my baby."
    },
    {
      "start": 405.83,
      "end": 407.87,
      "text": "It's so good."
    },
    {
      "start": 407.87,
      "end": 413.36,
      "text": "You shouldn't stay much."
    },
    {
      "start": 413.58,
      "end": 415.16,
      "text": "You should eat something."
    },
    {
      "start": 416.48,
      "end": 419.78,
      "text": "Yeah, last time, Rebecca and Ida had an argument."
    },
    {
      "start": 420.26,
      "end": 420.64,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 420.82,
      "end": 421.1,
      "text": "Seriously."
    },
    {
      "start": 421.46,
      "end": 423.14,
      "text": "When do they not have an argument?"
    },
    {
      "start": 423.6,
      "end": 426.6,
      "text": "This was the mother-in-law and daughter-in-law?"
    },
    {
      "start": 426.78,
      "end": 427.02,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 427.4,
      "end": 429.58,
      "text": "오늘은 좀 분위기가 괜찮아졌네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 429.58,
      "end": 431.58,
      "text": "After Abe ran away."
    },
    {
      "start": 431.58,
      "end": 433.14,
      "text": "Yeah, 상황이 상황인지라."
    },
    {
      "start": 433.14,
      "end": 434.4,
      "text": "Abe 도망갔어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 434.48,
      "end": 434.64,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 434.92,
      "end": 437.42,
      "text": "이제서 하회하는 모습."
    },
    {
      "start": 437.74,
      "end": 439.0,
      "text": "내용을 한 번 살펴보겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 440.04,
      "end": 441.68,
      "text": "I don't know what to do."
    },
    {
      "start": 442.02,
      "end": 443.42,
      "text": "I don't know what to do."
    },
    {
      "start": 443.58,
      "end": 444.3,
      "text": "네, Rebecca가 이야기했죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 444.3,
      "end": 448.92,
      "text": "무엇을 해야 할지 정말 모르겠어요라는 겁니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 449.72,
      "end": 451.2,
      "text": "Yeah, her son is gone."
    },
    {
      "start": 451.42,
      "end": 451.98,
      "text": "Sure."
    },
    {
      "start": 452.3,
      "end": 453.74,
      "text": "Who knows what to do."
    },
    {
      "start": 453.78,
      "end": 454.06,
      "text": "그러게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 454.16,
      "end": 455.66,
      "text": "정말 온몸이 덜덜 떨릴 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 455.7,
      "end": 457.1,
      "text": "They're like, should we call the police?"
    },
    {
      "start": 457.44,
      "end": 458.36,
      "text": "No, let's just wait."
    },
    {
      "start": 458.42,
      "end": 459.18,
      "text": "He'll come back."
    },
    {
      "start": 459.52,
      "end": 460.92,
      "text": "They're deciding what to do."
    },
    {
      "start": 460.96,
      "end": 461.14,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 462.14,
      "end": 462.84,
      "text": "It's okay."
    },
    {
      "start": 462.84,
      "end": 464.86,
      "text": "시어머니인 아이라가"
    },
    {
      "start": 464.86,
      "end": 465.88,
      "text": "It's okay."
    },
    {
      "start": 466.32,
      "end": 467.2,
      "text": "위로를 합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 467.98,
      "end": 470.58,
      "text": "There is no guidebook to be a parent."
    },
    {
      "start": 470.82,
      "end": 472.62,
      "text": "좋은 이야기도 해주시네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 472.64,
      "end": 473.42,
      "text": "That is true."
    },
    {
      "start": 473.58,
      "end": 474.54,
      "text": "No guidebook."
    },
    {
      "start": 475.02,
      "end": 476.44,
      "text": "I wish there were a guidebook."
    },
    {
      "start": 476.56,
      "end": 477.16,
      "text": "Oh, right."
    },
    {
      "start": 477.52,
      "end": 478.32,
      "text": "To be a parent."
    },
    {
      "start": 478.5,
      "end": 482.42,
      "text": "부모가 되기 위한 어떤 guidebook이 없다라는 문장이었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 482.48,
      "end": 484.28,
      "text": "There is no guidebook to be a parent."
    },
    {
      "start": 485.08,
      "end": 488.4,
      "text": "Hard to be one and hard to lose one."
    },
    {
      "start": 488.4,
      "end": 490.42,
      "text": "네, 이건 무슨 의미인지 아시겠죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 490.42,
      "end": 494.2,
      "text": "부모 노릇을 하는 것도 어렵지만"
    },
    {
      "start": 494.2,
      "end": 498.02,
      "text": "그렇다고 해서 부모 노릇을 잘하기 위한 것을"
    },
    {
      "start": 498.02,
      "end": 500.76,
      "text": "포기하는 것도 어렵다라는 이야기입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 501.0,
      "end": 503.12,
      "text": "Yeah, I think hard to lose one."
    },
    {
      "start": 503.24,
      "end": 505.9,
      "text": "That could mean like your mom or dad"
    },
    {
      "start": 505.9,
      "end": 507.62,
      "text": "when they pass away."
    },
    {
      "start": 507.66,
      "end": 508.3,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 508.84,
      "end": 511.76,
      "text": "네, 그럴 때도 이렇게 쓸 수 있겠죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 511.92,
      "end": 513.68,
      "text": "Yeah, so it's hard to be a parent"
    },
    {
      "start": 513.68,
      "end": 516.28,
      "text": "and it's hard to lose your mom or your dad."
    },
    {
      "start": 516.36,
      "end": 516.58,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 516.58,
      "end": 517.24,
      "text": "Very hard."
    },
    {
      "start": 517.48,
      "end": 518.64,
      "text": "Anyway, 아이라는"
    },
    {
      "start": 518.64,
      "end": 520.44,
      "text": "It's giving comforting words."
    },
    {
      "start": 520.82,
      "end": 522.42,
      "text": "Yes, she's being comforting."
    },
    {
      "start": 522.58,
      "end": 522.78,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 522.94,
      "end": 523.86,
      "text": "This is a good change."
    },
    {
      "start": 523.9,
      "end": 524.1,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 524.42,
      "end": 525.96,
      "text": "They're moving in a good direction."
    },
    {
      "start": 526.02,
      "end": 526.46,
      "text": "그러게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 527.57,
      "end": 529.57,
      "text": "He will come home, Habibi."
    },
    {
      "start": 530.11,
      "end": 530.59,
      "text": "Sorry."
    },
    {
      "start": 530.89,
      "end": 533.03,
      "text": "네, 이 Habibi라는 애칭 들으셨죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 533.15,
      "end": 533.81,
      "text": "지난번에도 한번 나왔습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 534.81,
      "end": 537.57,
      "text": "그래서 그때는 우리 에이브에게 Habibi 이랬는데"
    },
    {
      "start": 537.57,
      "end": 541.09,
      "text": "이번에는 며느리한테 Habibi라고 애칭을 불러줍니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 541.17,
      "end": 541.65,
      "text": "How sweet."
    },
    {
      "start": 541.85,
      "end": 542.07,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 542.35,
      "end": 544.33,
      "text": "He will come home, Habibi."
    },
    {
      "start": 544.33,
      "end": 545.63,
      "text": "이렇게 이야기했어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 546.05,
      "end": 547.35,
      "text": "그는 집에 올 거야."
    },
    {
      "start": 547.95,
      "end": 548.27,
      "text": "그러면서"
    },
    {
      "start": 548.27,
      "end": 549.03,
      "text": "Sorry."
    },
    {
      "start": 549.31,
      "end": 550.79,
      "text": "Oh, she apologizes."
    },
    {
      "start": 551.31,
      "end": 554.55,
      "text": "She was being very critical of her daughter-in-law"
    },
    {
      "start": 554.55,
      "end": 557.27,
      "text": "for not taking care of her son."
    },
    {
      "start": 557.39,
      "end": 557.69,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 557.83,
      "end": 559.67,
      "text": "Not even knowing where he is."
    },
    {
      "start": 559.89,
      "end": 563.65,
      "text": "So now she is apologizing for her words."
    },
    {
      "start": 563.75,
      "end": 563.97,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 564.19,
      "end": 566.63,
      "text": "이게 사과하는 의미도 있겠지만"
    },
    {
      "start": 566.63,
      "end": 570.49,
      "text": "또 다른 방면에는 좀 유감이다 라고 할 때도"
    },
    {
      "start": 570.49,
      "end": 572.17,
      "text": "사용이 가능한 표현이잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 572.17,
      "end": 572.81,
      "text": "그죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 572.89,
      "end": 574.33,
      "text": "It seems to have false meanings here."
    },
    {
      "start": 574.61,
      "end": 575.21,
      "text": "Yeah, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 575.85,
      "end": 577.35,
      "text": "Sorry your son ran away."
    },
    {
      "start": 577.45,
      "end": 577.71,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 578.09,
      "end": 580.01,
      "text": "And also sorry for what I said."
    },
    {
      "start": 580.23,
      "end": 581.29,
      "text": "That's right."
    },
    {
      "start": 582.09,
      "end": 582.85,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "start": 582.97,
      "end": 583.71,
      "text": "네, 그랬더니"
    },
    {
      "start": 583.71,
      "end": 584.85,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "start": 584.93,
      "end": 586.15,
      "text": "사과를 받아들인 거예요."
    },
    {
      "start": 586.31,
      "end": 587.47,
      "text": "아, 참 훈훈하다."
    },
    {
      "start": 587.91,
      "end": 588.23,
      "text": "좋아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 590.25,
      "end": 591.45,
      "text": "I'm losing steam."
    },
    {
      "start": 591.57,
      "end": 592.65,
      "text": "이거 남편이 한 말이죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 592.97,
      "end": 595.05,
      "text": "I'm losing steam 이라고 했습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 595.89,
      "end": 598.13,
      "text": "나 완전 진이 다 쇠했어."
    },
    {
      "start": 598.25,
      "end": 599.07,
      "text": "진이 다 빠졌어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 599.07,
      "end": 599.97,
      "text": "진이 빠졌다."
    },
    {
      "start": 600.07,
      "end": 601.29,
      "text": "That's a good expression."
    },
    {
      "start": 601.29,
      "end": 603.03,
      "text": "I'm losing steam."
    },
    {
      "start": 603.93,
      "end": 605.49,
      "text": "I think of a steam engine."
    },
    {
      "start": 605.73,
      "end": 608.09,
      "text": "If the steam all leaves the engine,"
    },
    {
      "start": 608.29,
      "end": 609.53,
      "text": "then it dies."
    },
    {
      "start": 609.65,
      "end": 610.43,
      "text": "Good imagination."
    },
    {
      "start": 610.81,
      "end": 611.75,
      "text": "It can't move."
    },
    {
      "start": 611.85,
      "end": 612.05,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 612.31,
      "end": 613.77,
      "text": "That's losing steam."
    },
    {
      "start": 613.83,
      "end": 615.03,
      "text": "너무 와닿는 표현입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 615.11,
      "end": 615.27,
      "text": "그죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 615.87,
      "end": 617.35,
      "text": "I can't see straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 617.45,
      "end": 619.61,
      "text": "네, 아까 배우셨던 표현 여기도 들리죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 619.69,
      "end": 620.97,
      "text": "I can't see straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 621.43,
      "end": 623.01,
      "text": "눈앞이 잘 안 보여요."
    },
    {
      "start": 623.07,
      "end": 623.87,
